// Negative fixture (issue #111): trait-coherence orphan rule (Part V §3 /
// §28.3). At most one `impl Trait for Head` may exist across the package
// graph — no specialization, no overlap. A second `impl Canonical for Order`
// must fail closed with BRX-LOW-0017 rather than silently picking a winner.
package neg.coherence @ 0.1.0

entity Order { key ref: String }

trait Canonical { type Item }

impl Canonical for Order { type Item = String }
impl Canonical for Order { type Item = String }
